# BREE Stack Monorepo Rules

This is the **bree-ai monorepo**. All development must strictly conform to the **BREE stack**:

| Layer | Technology                                                |
| ----- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| **B** | **Bun** — runtime, package manager, test runner           |
| **R** | **React 19** — frontend UI framework                      |
| **E** | **Elysia** — backend API framework                        |
| **E** | **Eden Treaty** (`@elysiajs/eden`) — type-safe API client |

---

## 🔴 ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS

The following are **never allowed** under any circumstances:

### Runtime & Package Manager

- ❌ **No Node.js** — never use `node` to run scripts or servers
- ❌ **No npm** — never use `npm install`, `npm run`, `npm ci`, etc.
- ❌ **No yarn** — not permitted
- ❌ **No pnpm** — not permitted
- ✅ **Only `bun`** — use `bun install`, `bun run`, `bunx`, `bun test`

### Language

- ❌ **No plain JavaScript files** — `.js` and `.mjs` files are not allowed in `src/` directories
- ❌ **No `require()`** — no CommonJS; use ESM `import`/`export` exclusively
- ✅ **TypeScript only** — all source files must be `.ts` or `.tsx`
- ✅ **Strict TypeScript** — `"strict": true` in all `tsconfig.json`

### Configuration Files (Exceptions)

- Config files that cannot be `.ts` (e.g., `postcss.config.js`, `tailwind.config.js`) are permitted as `.js` **only** when the tool requires it. These must use ESM (`import`/`export`), not CJS.

---

## ✅ REQUIRED PRACTICES

### Package Manager

```bash
# Installing dependencies
bun install

# Adding a package
bun add <package>
bun add -d <package>   # devDependency

# Running scripts
bun run dev
bun run build
bun test

# Running one-off scripts
bunx <tool>
```

### Monorepo Structure

```
bree-ai/
├── apps/           # Frontend React/Vite apps and backend Elysia servers
│   ├── <app-name>/
│   │   ├── src/           # TypeScript source only
│   │   ├── vite.config.ts # Frontend apps use Vite
│   │   └── package.json   # "type": "module"
├── packages/       # Shared internal packages (workspace:*)
│   └── bree-ai-core/
└── package.json    # Root workspace config
```

### `package.json` Requirements

Every `package.json` in this monorepo **must** have:

```json
{
  "type": "module"
}
```

Workspace dependencies must use `workspace:*`:

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "@bree-ai/core": "workspace:*"
  }
}
```

### Backend: Elysia APIs

All backend services must use **Elysia** with full type export:

```typescript
// src/index.ts
import { Elysia } from "elysia";

const app = new Elysia().get("/health", () => ({ status: "ok" })).listen(3000);

// REQUIRED: Always export the App type for Eden type-safety
export type App = typeof app;
```

Run with Bun — never Node:

```bash
bun run src/index.ts
```

### Frontend: Eden Treaty Client

All frontend apps must connect to Elysia APIs using **Eden Treaty**:

```typescript
// src/api/client.ts
import { edenTreaty } from "@elysiajs/eden";
import type { App } from "../../../api/src/index";

const url = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || "/";
export const api = edenTreaty<App>(url);
```

Never use raw `fetch()` for internal API calls — always use the typed Eden client.

### Frontend: Vite Configuration

Frontend apps use **Vite** (not Bun's bundler). The `vite.config.ts` **must** include:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import react from "@vitejs/plugin-react";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    react({
      jsxRuntime: "automatic",
      babel: false, // REQUIRED: Prevents _lruCache errors under Bun
    }),
  ],
});
```

### PostCSS Configuration

When using Tailwind CSS, `postcss.config.js` **must** use explicit imports (not the shorthand object syntax), or it will fail under Bun:

```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT
import tailwindcss from "tailwindcss";
import autoprefixer from "autoprefixer";

export default {
  plugins: [tailwindcss, autoprefixer],
};

// ❌ WRONG — causes "plugin is not a function" under Bun+Vite
export default {
  plugins: { tailwindcss: {}, autoprefixer: {} },
};
```

