## 📦 Approved Dependencies

| Purpose            | Package                             |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
| Backend framework  | `elysia`                            |
| API client         | `@elysiajs/eden`                    |
| Frontend framework | `react`, `react-dom`                |
| Build tool         | `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`      |
| Styling            | `tailwindcss`, `autoprefixer`       |
| Markdown rendering | `marked`                            |
| Validation         | `zod` (Elysia has built-in support) |
| Testing            | Bun's built-in test runner          |

---

## 🏗️ App Build Checklist

Before creating or modifying any app in this monorepo:

- [ ] `package.json` has `"type": "module"`
- [ ] All scripts use `bun` commands only
- [ ] All source files are `.ts` or `.tsx`
- [ ] Backend uses Elysia and exports `App` type
- [ ] Frontend uses Eden Treaty for all API calls
- [ ] `vite.config.ts` has `babel: false` in the React plugin
- [ ] `postcss.config.js` uses explicit imports (not object shorthand)
- [ ] No `node_modules/.gitignore` checked in
- [ ] Internal packages referenced with `workspace:*`

---

## 🚫 Code Anti-Patterns to Reject

```typescript
// ❌ Never: CommonJS require
const express = require("express");

// ❌ Never: Node-specific APIs as primary runtime
import { createServer } from "http";

// ❌ Never: Raw fetch for internal APIs
const res = await fetch("/api/users");

// ❌ Never: .js file extension on source files
// src/utils.js ← wrong

// ✅ Always: ESM imports
import { Elysia } from "elysia";

// ✅ Always: Eden Treaty for internal API calls
const res = await api.api.users.get();

// ✅ Always: TypeScript source files
// src/utils.ts ← correct
```
